<br>
It's a tough balance.  The point of &quot;Who wants to play a cheated-on spouse?&quot; is a good one, but what about, &quot;Who wants to play the spouse of a character they never see or hear from?&quot; is another.<br>
<br>
It's pretty bad when you're RPing a character almost every day, and your character's IC significant other's player vanishes for a couple of months.  And then they want to come back and act like they'd never been gone.  This happened to me back when I was freeform roleplaying in chatrooms.  When I decided to quit for what I knew would be at least a few months, I told my character's significant other's player, and gave him the option to break it off.  He decided that that would be best for the way he wanted to play, and I was fine with that.  It's somewhat rude, in my opinion, not to do so. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.members.shaw.ca/vae/velsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
