<br>
I suppose it gets down to for me whether a player affects a charector, or if a charector affects a player more. Personally, i think that Anything IC can be left in charector, and things like marriage in game doesn't need to be discussed beyond the obvious &quot;I'm not looking in RL, ect.&quot;. It belies a certain amount of suspence for &quot;what will happen to my charector today?&quot;, and even if that's drastic change such as getting divorced from a cheating spouse, it should be looked at as a part of the story of your charectors life, and only having to do with you and the other player because you control their ultimate fates.<br>
<br>
Still, if you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>want</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to have Roleplaying that is very regimented and structured, i suppose you could always ask your mate to give their charector's probably future actions as they might affect you. i just see no point. <p>----------------<br>
